{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a3db57a6-9352-4bf8-a472-b21f90cea515","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `.csproj`** — change the target framework:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`** — pin the new SDK:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — update base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\nThen run `dotnet restore` and `dotnet build` to verify everything compiles. Check for any NuGet packages with major version bumps (e.g., `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*`, `Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.*`) and update those to their 11.x versions as well.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"45c8432b-5789-41dd-9b14-8ab50ecae931","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question I can answer from knowledge — no codebase to explore.","outputTokens":272,"requestId":"E024:2F6FBA:77A7D54:8459F93:69F406BC"},"id":"3912cf41-2106-4843-b88d-dd9e84619b73","timestamp":"2026-05-01T01:49:54.470Z","parentId":"3cc0ea94-8232-4417-a60d-1f9f2e47a505"}
